Am Sat, Jun 24, 2023 at 03:56:19PM +0530 schrieb Nilesh Patra:
> Otherwise, do you want phylonium to support only 64-bit archs, and
> should we ask for removal of 32-bit entirely?

In case of leaf packages of Debian Med we can safely assume that they
are used on 64bit in practice.  Any mentionable time cycles we spent for
making it work on 32bit will stop us working on more valuable targets.
I do not say it does not make any sense to support 32bit - but we simply
have more important stuff to do IMHO.

